Find missing number (1 to n)
ChatGPT said:

Great choice üëç
Let‚Äôs solve Find Missing Number (1 to n) without using extra space.

Problem

Given an array of size n containing numbers from 0 to n (or 1 to n), one number is missing. Find the missing number.

Example

Input:

arr = [3, 0, 1]


Output:

2

Approaches
‚úÖ 1. Sum Formula

Expected sum = n*(n+1)/2

Actual sum = sum of array elements

Missing = Expected ‚Äì Actual

public class MissingNumber {
    public static int findMissing(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int expected = n * (n + 1) / 2;
        int actual = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            actual += num;
        }
        return expected - actual;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {3, 0, 1};
        System.out.println(findMissing(arr)); // 2
    }
}


‚è± Time: O(n)
üì¶ Space: O(1)

‚úÖ 2. XOR Method (No Overflow Risk)

XOR of all numbers from 0 to n

XOR of all elements in array

Missing = XOR of both

public class MissingNumberXOR {
    public static int findMissing(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int xor1 = 0, xor2 = 0;

        // XOR with numbers from 0..n
        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            xor1 ^= i;
        }

        // XOR with array elements
        for (int num : nums) {
            xor2 ^= num;
        }

        return xor1 ^ xor2;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {3, 0, 1};
        System.out.println(findMissing(arr)); // 2
    }
}
